The paper focuses on improving the efficiency and accuracy of 3D convolutional networks for video classification, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture that achieves better performance while being more efficient, which involves machine learning (cs.MM), and the paper also discusses the trade-offs between computation and accuracy, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
